<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-11-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-11-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="113" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d113">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Griscom</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.—Extract.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Petropolis</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-11-15"><hi rend="italic">November 15,
                                    1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Reports that he has been assured that the present tariff, including duty
                            on flour, will not be altered by this Congress, which expires December
                            31, and says that the existing preferential list is almost certain to be
                            continued for next year.)</p>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>